In review of this site, one may find almost anything posted. Just take a look at the number of threads dealing with diverse subjects.  However, most threads, as is typical in other conversations, drift off the subject.  There are heart rendoring searches for information about lost fathers, emotional tributes to the dead, and an almost desperate reaching out for acceptance. There is dark humor and light humor, a coy way of defuzing past horrors.  There is conclusion reached upon false premiss.  There is weak and strong justification for past actions.  There are strong convictions and those which are wavering.  Essentially, there is a tremendous need for enlightenment and endorsement...hence a brotherhood is born.  The most articulate writers often fail to convey the true essence of what is actually felt by two or more people...combat veterans.  Where direct words and gallant attempts to explain all fail...there seems to be left in its place some, yet to be spoken, truth to be derived from the attempts.  By osmosis, we suck up the unintelligible through hugs, handshakes, tears and ribald stories... still left wanting.<br>
It is natural that one boast his own deeds and the deeds of others, a common trait of man... food for pride and honor, a nurturing of the premiss that we do make a difference or have made a difference in the past.<br>
Perhaps this thread can serve those who wish to whisper sacred truths, free of anger, remorse and fear...if that is possible.<br><br>
Edward Ramon
